      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Concept ACK on updating the developer notes.\r\n\r\nPerhaps we could re-use the relevant recommendation from the C++ Core Guidelines (edited by our C++ friends Bjarne Stroustrup and Herb Sutter) including the nice table:\r\n\r\n> [F.15: Prefer simple and conventional ways of passing information](https://isocpp.github.io/CppCoreGuidelines/CppCoreGuidelines#Rf-conventional)\r\n>\r\n> Using Ã¢ÂÂunusual and cleverÃ¢ÂÂ techniques causes surprises, slows understanding by other programmers, and encourages bugs. If you really feel the need for an optimization beyond the common techniques, measure to ensure that it really is an improvement, and document/comment because the improvement may not be portable.\r\n> \r\n> Normal parameter passing:\r\n> \r\n> ![](https://isocpp.github.io/CppCoreGuidelines/param-passing-normal.png)\r\n> \r\n> Advanced parameter passing:\r\n> \r\n> ![](https://isocpp.github.io/CppCoreGuidelines/param-passing-advanced.png)\r\n> \r\n> Use the advanced techniques only after demonstrating need, and document that need in a comment.\r\n\r\nIf we want to use the text and/or the table the C++ Core Guidelines says the following:\r\n\r\n> We make this project available to Ã¢ÂÂfriendly usersÃ¢ÂÂ to use, copy, modify, and derive from, hoping for constructive input.",
